				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">It takes two bits to make each background pixel. Bit 0 of each pixel is stored in one plane ($xxx0-$xxx7), and bit 1 of each pixel is stored in the other plane ($xxx8-$xxxF). See <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Planar_%28computer_graphics%29" class="postlink">Planar graphics</a> and <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/PPU_pattern_tables" class="postlink">PPU pattern tables</a>.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

